{"kind":"project","sections":[{"estimatedTimeInMinutes":15,"kind":"hero","chapter":"Store Todos in a database","backgroundImage":"hummingbird.png","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Now we have a working API and a way to test it, lets look into storing our todos in a Postgres database with PostgresNIO.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"title":"Use PostgresNIO to store your Todos in a Postgres database","image":"hummingbird.png"},{"tasks":[{"contentSection":[{"mediaPosition":"trailing","media":"hummingbird.png","kind":"contentAndMedia","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Setup a Postgres database to use with the Todos application.","type":"text"}]}]}],"stepsSection":[{"runtimePreview":null,"type":"step","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You’ll need to install postgres on your system if you don’t already have it. Detailed instructions on installing Postgres can be found ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/www.postgresql.org\/download\/"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once you have installed Postgres follow the instructions on screen to start your Postgres database service."}]}],"media":null,"code":"todos-postgres-01.sh"},{"runtimePreview":null,"type":"step","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The Postgres install comes with ","type":"text"},{"code":"psql","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" the commandline interface to Postgres. We are going to use this to create a new database and a new role.","type":"text"}]}],"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Note the SQL commands all end in a semi-colon. The ","type":"text"},{"code":"\\c","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" command connects to a database and the ","type":"text"},{"code":"\\q","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" command quits "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pqsl"},{"type":"text","text":". You can find out more about